  "texts": [
    "The cloud server and malicious users cannot obtain a meaningful message from the encrypted data.",
    "The following scenarios were created for the security analysis of the proposed scheme.",
    "Suppose an attacker gains unauthorized access to data stored in the database.A patient's EMR is kept fragmented and encrypted in a database.",
    "Even if a patient's EMR falls into the hands of unauthorized individuals, it is not possible for these individuals to decrypt the encrypted data without the patient's storage list.",
    "An EMR is only meaningful to the patient who owns that data and third-party entities that the patient authorizes.Suppose an authorized third-party entity maliciously modifies or deletes the patient's EMR.The hash values of EMRs are kept on the blockchain for access control: HashðEMR p id Þ.These hash values on the blockchain cannot be changed."
